  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies arguments for instantiating a typeface variant, including variation coordinates, palette selection, and collection index.</summary>
    <remarks><format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[
## Remarks

`SKFontArguments` is a `ref struct` that bundles the parameters passed to
<xref:SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.Clone(SkiaSharp.SKFontArguments)> when creating a specific
instance of a variable or color font. It holds span-based references to variation
coordinates and palette overrides, so it cannot be stored on the heap.

This is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
// Clone a typeface using specific variation design coordinates
SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate[] coords =
[
    new SKFontVariationPositionCoordinate { Axis = SKFourByteTag.Parse("wght"), Value = 700 },
];
var args = new SKFontArguments
{
    VariationDesignPosition = coords,
};
using SKTypeface bold = typeface.Clone(args);
```
]]></format></remarks>
  </Docs>
